#DOC id=18--brain--wiki-knowledge source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/18--brain--wiki-knowledge.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.303Z

S|# 18 · Brain & Wiki (Knowledge)|> The mem system, visualized as a **3D knw graph** you can fly through, plus a searchable **Library** of the MD files the agents create. Everything is vectorized in Supabase with semantic search for all agents.
S|Purpose|The shared mem/wiki for the whole org. It both **visualizes** how knw is forming (a 3D graph of connected topics) and lets the owner **navigate** the underlying documents. The new mem system is what makes the Advisory Council and agents far smarter than the old narrow-knw setup.
S|Page header|- Title: **Brain & Wiki**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / Brain & Wiki`. // - Global search ("Ask Henry or jump anywhere…"). // - **View toggle: Graph \| Library**. // - **Visibility filter chips**: **All areas**, **Private**, **Team**, **Workspace**, **Cross-WS** (cross-workspace) — filter the knw by who can see it. // - Counters top-right: **Topics** (e.g. 248), **Documents** (e.g. 3,412), and a small alert count (e.g. 7).
S|Graph view (3D knowledge map)|- A **3D force-directed graph** of glowing nodes (topics) connected by edges, color-coded (purple/teal/yellow) — likely by visibility or workspace. // - **Interactions:** hover a node to see the topic; **zoom** in/out; **click a node** to open its detail (see below). The camera can orbit the cluster. // - Node **size** reflects how much knw is built around a topic; clusters show how knw areas are developing. // ### Node detail (click popup / right panel) // Clicking a node opens a detail panel, 
S|"What the agents know" (right rail, graph view)|- A live panel summarizing the knw base and **gaps/alerts** — e.g. "No data on TikTok Shop fees," "Missing cp thumbnail teardown," "Valhalla venue contacts incomplete" — each with an **Account / fix** action. This turns missing knw into actionable tasks.
S|Library view|- A **doc browser** of all the MD files the mem system has created. // - **Filter by category** and **sort** controls to quickly navigate. // - Each doc row shows title, category, visibility, source, and last-updated; selecting one opens the doc with its **Answer / Findings / sources** structure. // - Example doc opened: *"is agt-as-a-service real demand?"* showing an **Answer**, **Findings** (with inline source chips/links), and **"What this means for us"** synthesis — i.e. mem entries are stru
S|Technical model (stated)|- Built on **Supabase**. // - **Everything is vectorized**; **semantic search is enabled for all agents** so any agt can retrieve relevant mem. // - Visibility scoping (Private / Team / Workspace / Cross-workspace) controls which agents can access which knw.
S|Why it matters|This is the backbone that gives every agt (and especially the Advisory Council) complete, shared ctx — the single biggest upgrade over the old system's siloed, narrow knw.